The paper involves the development of a simulation environment and training of a deep reinforcement learning agent for autonomous lane changing, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of simulation and training of a deep learning agent also suggests the possibility of computer vision (cs.CV) being involved. Additionally, the paper deals with the challenges of uncertainty and safety in a dynamic traffic environment, which could also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
